The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	East Bengal have decided to retain Subhas Bhowmick as coach for the next season. The executive committee of the club has already spoken to the coach and discussed recruitment plans.       
	Bhowmick had replaced Stanley Rozario after the end of the first leg of the I-League.       
	There was dissent among some officials over Bhowmicks role in the teams performance in the ongoing I-League. However, the clubs senior officials discussed the issue on Monday and were learnt to have kept faith in him. A formal announcement is expected to be made after the clubs emergent executive committee meeting on Tuesday.          
	 Sourav Ganguly condoled the death of his childhood coach Buddhadeb Banerjee, who died at a city nursing home Monday.       
	He was 63, and among Souravs early coaches at Dukhiram Cricket Coaching Centre. The former India captain placed a wreath on the body of Banerjee when it arrived at the CAB in the morning.          
	 CCFC emerged winners in the six-a-side cricket meet organised by the Umpires of CAB. In the final they defeated VCK.          
	 Paddlers from different districts will participate in the Calcutta Table Tennis Championship, scheduled to be held at the Khudiram Anushilan Kendra from April 10. The last date for entries to the four-day meet is April 7.                                                                                                                                                                       
